<p>When most people think of Miami, they think South Beach — and for good reason! The area’s most iconic spot is steeped in glamour as well as history. It also happens to feature some of the poshest spots in town.</p>
<p>Go shopping along the captivating Lincoln Road Mall, a pedestrians-only thoroughfare lined with boutique shops and cafes. You can catch your morning coffee at News Cafe, a moderately priced piece of South Beach history that’s ideal for people watching.</p>
<p>For drinks and dancing, you can hit up one of South Beach’s famous “VIP” clubs, like LIV, Basement, or Wall Lounge. Or, if you want something more laid back, go to the hidden cabana at Freehand Miami to get some handcrafted cocktails mixed with organic ingredients picked fresh from their garden.</p>
<h2>Take a Romantic Beachside Stroll in Key Biscayne</h2>
<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m28!1m12!1m3!1d28755.601302936233!2d-80.22208478630927!3d25.72262280387623!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m13!3e0!4m5!1s0x88d9b5f6594fa365%3A0xecf8e502280e8ed3!2sKey+Biscayne%2C+FL!3m2!1d25.693713!2d-80.1628248!4m5!1s0x88d9b79854e5fa2d%3A0xd88397e6cde5afb6!2sSteinger%2C+Iscoe+%26+Greene%2C+2333+Ponce+de+Leon+Blvd+%23920%2C+Coral+Gables%2C+FL+33134!3m2!1d25.7501201!2d-80.25845369999999!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1546529364280" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m28!1m12!1m3!1d28755.243660627566!2d-80.22232678630769!3d25.72410195383317!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m13!3e0!4m5!1s0x88d9b79854e5fa2d%3A0xd88397e6cde5afb6!2sSteinger%2C+Iscoe+%26+Greene%2C+2333+Ponce+de+Leon+Blvd+%23920%2C+Coral+Gables%2C+FL+33134!3m2!1d25.7501201!2d-80.25845369999999!4m5!1s0x88d9b5f6594fa365%3A0xecf8e502280e8ed3!2sKey+Biscayne%2C+FL!3m2!1d25.693713!2d-80.1628248!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1546529382979" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<p>Key Biscayne is like a little slice of isolated paradise just outside the city. You can avoid the crowds of South Beach and enjoy a much more private seaside stroll at Crandon Park. For the young at heart, you can both ride the iconic beachside carousel.</p>
<p>If you want even more privacy and a dose of adventure, you can travel south down the key to visit Bill Baggs Cape Florida State Park. This protected ecosystem offers miles of unspoiled sands as well as native trees to give you shade. Try your hand at wildlife spotting, or rent a sea kayak to soak in the majesty of the Atlantic first-hand.</p>
<h2>Sample Miami’s Distinctive Culture in Historic Little Havana</h2>
<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m28!1m12!1m3!1d14373.509339355334!2d-80.24778671166511!3d25.758097288213044!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m13!3e0!4m5!1s0x88d9b6f0a8f37c7d%3A0x2628ab19cadcfdf!2s1600+SW+8th+St%2C+Miami%2C+FL+33135!3m2!1d25.7655517!2d-80.2206779!4m5!1s0x88d9b79854e5fa2d%3A0xd88397e6cde5afb6!2sSteinger%2C+Iscoe+%26+Greene%2C+Ponce+de+Leon+Boulevard%2C+Coral+Gables%2C+FL!3m2!1d25.7501201!2d-80.25845369999999!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1546529327407" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m28!1m12!1m3!1d14373.534147773456!2d-80.24865246166522!3d25.75789233821452!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m13!3e0!4m5!1s0x88d9b79854e5fa2d%3A0xd88397e6cde5afb6!2sSteinger%2C+Iscoe+%26+Greene%2C+Ponce+de+Leon+Boulevard%2C+Coral+Gables%2C+FL!3m2!1d25.7501201!2d-80.25845369999999!4m5!1s0x88d9b6f0a8f37c7d%3A0x2628ab19cadcfdf!2s1600+SW+8th+St%2C+Miami%2C+FL+33135!3m2!1d25.7655517!2d-80.2206779!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1546529287066" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<p>One of the most utterly unique spots in the world, Little Havana offers sights, sounds, and flavors you could never find anywhere else. For traditional Cuban eats, try La Carreta. Couples looking for something a bit more unconventional would enjoy Cardon y el Tirano, which has an intimate dining room and a chef who’s unafraid to bend expectations. </p>
<p>LeKoké Wine & Bites is the place to be for wine lovers. It features reasonably priced Spanish tapas and a wine menu filled to bursting with over 300 selections.</p>
<p>Make sure to stop by Azucar for unbeatable ice cream that’s perfect for eating while you amble down 8th street absorbing the street art or visiting charming specialty shops.</p>
<p>At night, the place to be is the storied Ball & Chain club. Recently reopened, the club offers salsa dancing, live music, and other amazing experiences just about every night of the week.</p>
<h2>Get Outside the City for an Unforgettable Escape</h2>
